Anglo American, Brimstone and Gold Fields: South African Equities Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-18T05:57:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/anglo-brimstone-gold-fields-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index fell for a
third day, losing 55.21, or 0.2 percent, to 32,722.91 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.    African Rainbow Minerals Ltd . (ARI SJ): The South African
mining company expects earnings per share of between 7.10 rand
and 7.50 rand for the half-year through December, compared with
2.13 rand a year earlier. The stock slipped 1 rand, or 0.4
percent, to 231.50 rand.    Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): The diversified mining company
that makes up 11 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock index
releases earnings for the year ended December. Anglo fell 4.88
rand, or 1.3 percent, to 381.07 rand.  Brimstone Investment Corp. (BRN SJ): The investment holding
company said earnings per share excluding one-time items
probably increased to between 1.62 rand to 1.94 rand in the year
ended December, compared with 1.31 rand a year earlier.
Brimstone shares rose 0.2 percent to 5.60 rand.    Gold Fields Ltd . (GFI SJ): Africa’s second-largest producer
of the precious metal releases fourth-quarter earnings. The
stock rose 1.72 rand, or 1.5 percent, to 120.53 rand.  Hospitality Property Fund Ltd. (HPA SJ): The investor in
hotels and resorts said its income fell to 42.8 million rand ($6
million) in the six months through December from 56.7 million
rand a year earlier. Hyprop was unchanged at 13.80 rand.    Howden Africa Holdings Ltd . (HWN SJ), a maker of equipment
to handle air, gas and liquids forecast earnings per share from
continuing operations to be between 88 cents and 119 cents for
the year through December, which compares with the earnings of
152.48 cents from continuing operations a year earlier. Howden
was unchanged at 9.90 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:    Anglo American Plc  (AAUKY US) declined 1.3 percent to
$26.45. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) jumped 2.3 percent to
$47.30. BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) dropped 2 cents to $79.67.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) rose 0.2 percent to $4.60. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) jumped 1.5 percent to $16.82. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) was unchanged at $11.04. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) gained 1.7 percent to $29.75. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
rose 1.1 percent to $5.40. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) increased 0.4
percent to $51.03.  To contact the reporter on this story:
